# 🔔 Reminder Module — Frontend Implementation Plan

> **No code changes yet** — this is the design blueprint for your approval.

---

## 📁 Files to Create (3 new files)

### 1. `src/services/reminderService.ts`
API service layer — thin wrapper around your 9 backend endpoints.

| Function | Calls | Returns |
|---|---|---|
| `setReminder(leadId, body)` | `POST /api/reminders/lead/{leadId}` | `Reminder_Response_DTO` |
| `getMyDueReminders(page, size)` | `GET /api/reminders/me/due/page/{p}/size/{s}` | `Page<Reminder>` |
| `getMyMissedReminders(page, size)` | `GET /api/reminders/me/missed/page/{p}/size/{s}` | `Page<Reminder>` |
| `getMyPendingReminders(page, size)` | `GET /api/reminders/me/pending/page/{p}/size/{s}` | `Page<Reminder>` |
| `getMyReminders(page, size)` | `GET /api/reminders/me/{page}/{size}` | `Page<Reminder>` |
| `getRemindersByScore(score, page, size)` | `GET /api/reminders/me/score/{score}/page/{p}/size/{s}` | `Page<Reminder>` |
| `markAsSeen(reminderId)` | `PUT /api/reminders/{id}/seen` | `Reminder` |
| `updateReminder(reminderId, body)` | `PUT /api/reminders/{id}` | `Reminder` |
| `cancelReminder(reminderId)` | `DELETE /api/reminders/{id}` | `Reminder` |

