## 🔧 Admin Page Enhancement

### Option A: Standalone Admin Reminder View
For the Admin page, the **same `ReminderDashboard` component** works since the backend APIs (`/me/*`) return data based on the logged-in user's JWT token.

- **Admin** sees their own reminders (if they've set any)
- No special admin-only reminder endpoints exist in the backend currently

### Option B: Future Enhancement (requires backend changes)
If you later want Admins to see **all counselors' reminders**, you'd need a new backend endpoint like `GET /api/reminders/all/page/{p}/size/{s}`. For now, the existing APIs are user-scoped.

