## ❓ Questions Before I Start Coding

1. **Bell icon in header** — Your `Dashboard.jsx` already has a `<Bell>` icon in the header bar. Should clicking it show a dropdown of due/missed reminders (quick preview), or just navigate to the Reminders page?

2. **Real-time notifications** — Your backend has WebSocket support (`spring-boot-starter-websocket`). Do you want reminders to push live notifications when they trigger, or is polling (refresh on tab switch) enough for now?

3. **Admin view** — Should Admins only see their own reminders, or do you want a "view all counselors' reminders" feature? (This would need a new backend endpoint.)

4. **Which page first?** — Should I start with the Counselor page (MyLeadsFeed + Set Reminder button) or the standalone Reminder Dashboard?
